<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="718" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[113,648,1622,1699]" pageId="25" pageNumber="718">
ETYMOLOGY. — The species name “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ernst &amp; Fernández &amp; Fernández-Martínez &amp; Vera" authorityYear="2012" box="[478,574,1622,1646]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Rhabdomesidae" genus="Vidronovella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cryptostomida" pageId="25" pageNumber="718" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="elegantula">
<emphasis box="[478,574,1622,1646]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="718">elegantula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the small size and general delicate appearance of the new species (derived from Latin “elegans” = elegant).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
